20: Very well. Then let it be done.
25:
Excuse me, Your Highness—er,
Princess Lilith. How exactly do you
plan on using alchemy for our cause?
29:
Don't worry so much about
formalities, Light. You can address
me by title if you wish, but just "Lilith"
is fine as well.
32:
The three of us were just talking
about... this.
36:
A Curse Crystal?! How did you
manage to—
40:
The curse of the dark dragon dwells
within crystals such as this—with
enough power to corrupt even the
Starbreaker.
43:
Yet that is but one use of its
functions. We need to harness its
power, not fear it.
48:
In essence, it's a tool to record
information. Much like a piece of
paper, or a vinyl record.
52:
Tch... If a record could hold enough
power to alter reality itself, that is.
57:
Curse Crystals have great value in
the realm of alchemy. As such, they
are a precious natural resource for
our people.
62:
B-but... given the inevitable
expansion of the Abyss, I thought
the plan was to abandon our home
world.
66:
It still is. With the threat of the
Purgers gone, this is our chance to
utilize what we can before
everything is beyond reach.
70:
That is to say... We will be
establishing a Curse Crystal mining
operation!
75:
To pull that off, we'll need the
manpower, resources, and
technology to do so.
79:
Not to mention risk management. I'll
be there to run interference.
85:
P-please keep a good eye on them,
Bryce! You need to be the voice of
reason!
91:
Niiice! This sounds like a plan I can
sink my claws into.
95:
Claudius, I hope that I can count on
your help. Your people's knowledge
of mining would be invaluable to us.
98:
Any assistance you could provide
with equipment would also be
greatly appreciated.
102:
Sure, we can help! The crew totally
freaked out after the last shift we
had, but I'm sure they're over it by
now!
106:
If it's manpower you need, we could
also dispatch some of our personnel
to aid you.
110:
With the technology of Shibuya and
the Endless Blue, things should
proceed quite smoothly. Count on
us whenever you need engineering
expertise.
115:
Drone technology would come in
handy for such an operation. Of
course, if you're interested in making
any purchases, we would be happy
to oblige.
120:
The main problem then becomes
one of distribution.
126:
Clearly, we have much to discuss.
Let us make this operation a fruitful
one for us all!
133:
Phew... That takes care of one
problem.
137: You worked very hard. Well done.
141:
Thank you, Stella. You must be busy
with the school's reopening and
graduation ceremony coming up.
How are your interviews coming
along?
146:
Wonderfully. The hard part is putting
them all together...
150:
Speaking of plans for the future, I
have been meaning to ask...
153:
What of your lineage, Lilith? Do you
plan to produce an heir?
159:
*gasp* E-Estel! You mustn't ask such
things in polite company!
163:
My apologies. Was I lacking in tact?
But as the one who bears the crown,
you must consider such matters.
168:
Y'know, Qualia City has plenty of
options to explore in that field.
171:
These kinds of experiments might
not always end well, but I hear you
can pick your kid's sex and
everything. DAN's got their own
division too, right?
177:
Well, yes. But we tend to have a
hand in everything.
187:
Erm, I think I'd rather go the more...
traditional route for the heir-making
process—b-but this is no
conversation to be having during
lunch!
192:
Oh. Is it one we can have at night,
then?
197:
Um, I mean... I have the same, how
shall I put it—needs—as everyone
else. I... I think!
200:
What I mean to say is that I have
considered it, but not as a means to
control the throne. In fact, I am
thinking of dismantling the
monarchy altogether.
204:
Throughout their histories, other
worlds have taken a more
democratic approach to
government. Without bloodlines or
succession.
209:
Just take care that you don't end up
as the next Qualia City... Trust me,
that's the last thing you want.
217:
If that is truly what you wish, then so
be it. It is your future, after all... We
cannot stay together forever.
221:
Hehe! It's still a bit too early for you
to be feeling lonely!
224:
But all this talk of technological
advancements has me
thinking—does Qualia City have the
means to restore someone's sight?
228:
Ah, well, we've got the tech, sure. But
it doesn't really work on people from
other worlds...
231:
Unfortunately, I think Qualia City's a
no-go in that department. Still, that's
not enough to make you give up,
right?
235:
Of course not. Thank you for the
information nevertheless.
241:
Golem Hunting Season is now in full
swing! Entry number, uh... ten? Alk,
representing Starview Village!
254:
Excuse me, Lilith. I will join the fray,
as well.
259:
Hmph. I shan't let myself be left
behind either.
262:
As princess of the former Kingdom
of Stratos and acting leader of our
allied forces...
265: I, Lilith Stratos, will join the hunt!
269: I shall make you proud, Shakari!
